  <custodhist id="aspace_be47ede82eedddaf0ea4a73804ca88ae">
    <head>Custodial History</head>
<p>The Record of Milk Purchased ledgers were acquired for the University of Connecticut by Professor E. A. Perregaux in the late 1940s or early 1950s. They were stored in the Wilbur Cross Library until 1979, when they were transferred to the Historical Manuscripts and Archives Division of the University Libraries.</p>  </custodhist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_90c54b17db30e976f72054a4b34acaab">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>[Item description, #:#], Connecticut Milk Producers Association Records. Archives &amp; Special Collections at the Thomas J. Dodd Research Center, University of Connecticut Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_00c4373728fe1d4b20974db5b92c71fc">
    <head>Acquisition Information</head>
<p>The <title render="italic">Bulletins</title> were originally sent from the Connecticut Milk Producers Association to the Economic Service of Connecticut State College(now University of Connecticut). The Library collected the <title render="italic">Bulletins</title>  and bound them into five volumes. They were moved to the Archives in 1993 to become part of the CMPA collection. The correspondence and records of the association auditor and accountant, Irving Goldblatt, were donated in April 2011 by his family.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_01af7b614dbf013df18794773d46b0bd">
    <head>Access</head>
<p>The collection is open and available for research.</p>  </accessrestrict>
